{
  "text": "Sjo\u00a8gren's syndrome (SS) is an 'autoimmune epithelitis' characterized by sicca syndrome but also extra-glandular manifestations that reveal the severity of this disorder [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . SS can occur alone as primary SS (pSS) or accompany other autoimmune disorders as secondary SS (sSS) [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
